data.text: During the past 24 hours, no new admissions (due to COVID-19 complications) were registered in the Province, with the total number of admitted currently standing at 17.

The Province embarked in data cleaning in order to address backlogs, as such the number of people who have recovered from the disease surpassed the 100 000 mark, currently standing at 100 851. The average recovery rate stands at 93% and the active cases decreasing to 4 418.
There were no new deaths (related to COVID-19 complications) that occurred within the past 72 hours, thus the total cumulative deaths stand at 3 212.
Today's average positivity rate stand at 5%. All districts in the Province reported less than 5 new cases, except Namakwa with no new infections reported in the past 24 hours.
